-- Saks posts higher quarterly profit
-- 
-- Wed Mar 5, 2008 8:11am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/05/us-saks-results-idUSWNAS360620080305

 

 ATLANTA  (Reuters) - Upscale retailer Saks Inc SKS.N reported higher quarterly profit on Wednesday as demand for its updated goods helped boost sales in a challenging environment. 

 Earnings came to $39.5 million, or 26 cents a share, for the fourth quarter ended February 2, compared with $21.5 million, or 14 cents a share, a year earlier. (Reporting by  Karen Jacobs ; Editing by Gerald E. McCormick)